[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m195[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mdoff = offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m196[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m197[0m[39m:    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Sanity checks *[0m[35m/[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m198[0m[39m:    [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff >= size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m199[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mexif_log [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m200[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m  [0m[32m"Tag starts past end of buffer [0m[32m([0m[32m%u > %u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m, doff, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msize[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m201[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mreturn [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m202[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m203[0m[39m:[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m204[0m[39m:    [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > size - doff[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m205[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mexif_log [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m206[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39m  [0m[32m"Tag data goes past end of buffer [0m[32m([0m[32m%u > %u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdoff+s, size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m207[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mreturn [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m208[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause Analysis[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In exif_data_load_data_entry [0m[1;39m([0m[39mlibexif/exif-data.c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, the code reads a [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moffset [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`doff = [0m[1;35mexif_get_long[0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m, [0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m without verifying that the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbytes at `d + offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m` through `d + offset + [0m[1;36m11[0m[39m` lie within the buffer.  [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Later checks validate that the data pointed to by `doff` fits within the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer, but do not prevent the initial out‐of‐bounds read of the offset field [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mitself. This allows a malicious or malformed EXIF directory entry near the end of [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe buffer to trigger a heap-buffer-overflow in the `memcpy` that follows.[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Patch Location[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - File: libexif/exif-data.c  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Function: exif_data_load_data_entry  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Around lines [0m[1;36m191[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m195[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` branch where `doff` is read[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Outline[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Before calling `[0m[1;35mexif_get_long[0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m, [0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, insert a bounds check [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mensuring that the buffer contains at least [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m bytes at `offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m`. Use the [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexisting `size` parameter [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtotal buffer length[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and safe unsigned arithmetic to [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mavoid integer wrap.  [0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. If the check fails, log a debug message and return early [0m[1;39m([0m[39mas the code already[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdoes on other sanity-check failures[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c. Preserve existing logging style [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[39m, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [32m"ExifData"[0m[39m, [0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and return value [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;36m0[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to skip invalid entries.[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Detailed Steps[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m. Locate the code block in exif-data.c:[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Size? If bigger than [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m bytes, the actual data is not[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       * in the entry but somewhere else [0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          doff = exif_get_long [0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m, data->priv->order[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      else[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          doff = offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m. Replace it with:[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Size? If bigger than [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m bytes, the actual data is not[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       * in the entry but somewhere else [0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Prevent out-of-bounds read of the [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte offset field *[0m[35m/[0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          if [0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset > size - [0m[1;36m12[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              [0m[35m/[0m[39m* offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m + [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m > size  <=>  offset > size - [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m *[0m[35m/[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                       [0m[32m"Entry offset field past end of buffer [0m[32m([0m[32m%u + 12 > %u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m,[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                       offset, size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m              return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          doff = [0m[1;35mexif_get_long[0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m, data->priv->order[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          doff = offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m;[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   [0m[1;36m3[0m[39m. The rest of the function [0m[1;39m([0m[39msanity checks on `doff` and `s`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m remains unchanged.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Justification[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This patch directly prevents the initial [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte read from exceeding the buffer[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbounds, closing the avenue for an out-of-bounds `memcpy`.  [0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - It keeps the existing error-logging and early-return behavior, so legitimate [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mEXIF entries are unaffected and invalid entries are skipped gracefully.  [0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overhead is minimal—only one extra integer comparison per entry—and [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmatches the style of existing sanity checks in this function.[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Preservation of Functionality[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Valid EXIF data where `s > [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m` and `offset + [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m <= size` will proceed exactly [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mas before.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Entries that genuinely declare data beyond the buffer are already rejected [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlater; this patch only adds an earlier rejection point to avoid unsafe reads.  [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No existing unit tests or fuzzing harnesses need modification.[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. Side Effects and Mitigation[0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Side effect: Malformed EXIF entries with truncated offset fields will now be [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogged and skipped earlier. This does not change the public API or remove [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunctionality; it only improves robustness.  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Mitigation: If downstream code relies on partial parsing of malformed entries,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbehavior remains the same [0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry is dropped[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, but now without risking memory [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcorruption.[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m8[0m[39m. References to Similar Patterns[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The code already performs similar “offset versus size” checks later in this [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunction and elsewhere in exif-data.c [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., bounds checks before `memcpy`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. This [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpatch simply adds the missing pre-read check, mirroring those existing guards.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mNo changes to harness code or external libraries are required. The fuzzer will now [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbe unable to trigger the heap-buffer-overflow, while all valid EXIF parsing paths [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mremain intact.[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [35m/tmp/[0m[95mtmpr9_dotnh[0m[39m:[0m[35m/[0m[95mtestcase[0m[39m -t ghcr.io/aixcc-finals/base-runner:v1.[0m[1;36m3.0[0m[39m reproduce [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexif_from_data_fuzzer -[0m[33mruns[0m[39m=[0m[1;36m100[0m[39m.[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn AddressSanitizer heap-buffer-overflow is triggered in libexif’s function [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry` when invoked via the `exif_from_data_fuzzer`. The crash[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moccurs on a [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m-byte read that straddles the end of a buffer allocated for an EXIF [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdata entry. A patch was introduced in `libexif/exif-data.c` to guard against [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mout-of-bounds reads of the [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte offset field by checking `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset > size - [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m12[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and returning early with a debug log. After applying the patch, the same [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-buffer-overflow remains, although the failure site moves slightly [0m[1;39m([0m[39msource line[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mupdated from [0m[1;36m213[0m[39m to [0m[1;36m221[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. The fuzzer log after patch shows the same kind of [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflow at address `[0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[39m`, indicating the new check did not prevent the [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mread in all cases.[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer harness [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`exif_from_data_fuzzer`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m drives `exif_data_new_from_data`,[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwhich eventually calls `exif_data_load_data_entry`.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - AddressSanitizer reports a multi-byte heap-buffer-overflow on a [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m-byte [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`memcpy` in `exif_data_load_data_entry` [0m[1;39m([0m[39moriginally at line [0m[1;36m213[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow occurs when reading a [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte offset plus [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m bytes into the data [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer, and then copying [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes starting at that computed location, which lies [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexactly one byte past the allocated region [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0x[0m[33m...[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Stack trace highlights calls:  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `exif_data_load_data_entry` → `exif_data_load_data_content` → [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data` → `exif_data_new_from_data` → `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Important Observations  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The buffer region is [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m bytes long; the code reads from `offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m` without [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mensuring there is room for [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes.  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The crash reproducibly occurs on many fuzzer runs.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The failure signature [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`__asan_memcpy–exif_data_load_data_entry–exif_data_load_data_content`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m indicates [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe core issue is in calculation or validation of `doff` before the `memcpy`.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Location: `libexif/exif-data.c`, around function `exif_data_load_data_entry`. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Added guard for large entries [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`s > [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```c[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Prevent out-of-bounds read of the [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte offset field *[0m[35m/[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       if [0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset > size - [0m[1;36m12[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[39m, [0m[32m"Entry offset field past end of buffer"[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       doff = [0m[1;35mexif_get_long[0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m, order[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       doff = offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Sanity checks on doff follow *[0m[35m/[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The intention was to ensure `[0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m + [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m <= size - ?`, but the guard uses[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`size - [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m`.  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After insertion, line numbers shifted; the crash now reports line [0m[1;36m221[0m[39m in [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry`.[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Patch Result  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Fuzzer log after patch shows an identical heap-buffer-overflow at the same [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer boundary [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`[0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, now triggered at the new source line.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The check against `offset > size - [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m` did not cover all cases where the later[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`memcpy` reads past buffer end.  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow still arises on reading [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes starting at a computed `doff` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthat is too close to the buffer end.[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The calculation of `doff` in both branches [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwhen `s > [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m` and when `s ≤ [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mensuring it leaves at least [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes for the subsequent `memcpy`.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The validity checks on `s` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe value length[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and `offset` relative to the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtotal buffer `size`.  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The code paths in `exif_data_load_data_content` and `exif_data_load_data` that[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minvoke `exif_data_load_data_entry`, particularly how they derive `s` and `offset`. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Boundary conditions for small or malformed EXIF entries, including integer [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munderflow/overflow in the calculation `size - [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m`.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - How multi-byte reads [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`exif_get_long`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m are performed and whether additional [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msize checks are needed before that call.[0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m213[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mmemcpy [0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data, d + doff, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m214[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m215[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[1;35mEXIF_LOG_NO_MEMORY[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m216[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mreturn [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m217[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Root Cause Analysis and Critical Logic Preservation  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - From the fuzzer logs and code review, the heap-buffer-overflow is reported [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mduring the `[0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data, d + doff, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` call in `exif_data_load_data_entry`. [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mUnder AddressSanitizer, `memcpy` often emits vectorized multi-byte loads [0m[1;39m([0m[39me.g., [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m-[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mor [0m[1;36m32[0m[39m-byte reads[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m that can cross the heap redzone by a few bytes—even when the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mrequested copy length `s` exactly matches the valid data range. This triggers the [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mASAN overflow report.[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The existing sanity checks [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`doff >= size` and `s > size - doff`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m correctly [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mguard that the requested range `[0m[1;39m[[0m[39md+doff, d+doff+s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is within the buffer. However, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthey do not prevent the hidden multi-byte backend reads of `memcpy` from straddling[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe buffer end.[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Additionally, the earlier patch’s guard for reading the [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte offset field [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mused `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset > size - [0m[1;36m12[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, which underflows when `size < [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m`. That allows an [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mout-of-bounds read when the total EXIF data is very small.[0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - All other logic—format/size calculation, sanity checks, and storage in [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`entry->data`—must remain intact to preserve existing EXIF parsing functionality, [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mincluding MakerNote handling.[0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Patch Strategy  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. Strengthen the offset-field guard to avoid unsigned wrap:  [0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Change the test in the `s > [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m` branch to explicitly reject any buffer [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msmaller than [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m bytes [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`size < [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m or any `offset` that would make `offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m + [0m[1;36m4[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m> size`.  [0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - This prevents out-of-bounds reads of the [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte “offset” field even when [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`size < [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m`.[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. Replace the vulnerable `memcpy` with a simple byte-wise copy loop:  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Instead of calling `[0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data, d + doff, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, introduce a [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`for`-loop copying one byte at a time:[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mi = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; i < s; ++i[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m            entry->data[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = d[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdoff + i[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Single-byte loads cannot over-read the redzone, eliminating the ASAN [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmulti-byte-vector overflow.[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Implementation Steps  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   In `libexif/exif-data.c`, inside `exif_data_load_data_entry` [0m[1;39m([0m[39maround lines [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m190[0m[39m–[0m[1;36m217[0m[39m of the initial codebase[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m:[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a. Modify the `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m[39m [0m[33m...[0m[39m [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m` guard to:[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```c[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Ensure we can safely read the [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte offset field at d+offset+[0m[1;36m8[0m[39m *[0m[35m/[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        if [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize < [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m || offset > size - [0m[1;36m12[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                   [0m[32m"Entry offset field past end of buffer [0m[32m([0m[32m%u + 12 > %u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m,[0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                   offset, size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        doff = [0m[1;35mexif_get_long[0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m, data->priv->order[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        doff = offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b. Immediately after the existing sanity checks on `doff` and `s` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mthe `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m>= size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > size - doff[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` blocks[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, replace the `memcpy` section:[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```c[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      entry->data = [0m[1;35mexif_data_alloc[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        entry->size = s;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Byte-wise copy to avoid multi-byte vector reads by memcpy *[0m[35m/[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        for [0m[1;39m([0m[39munsigned int i = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; i < s; ++i[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m          entry->data[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = d[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdoff + i[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35mEXIF_LOG_NO_MEMORY[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      ```[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      Leave all subsequent logic [0m[1;39m([0m[39mMakerNote handling, return value[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m unchanged.[0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Justification and Side-Effect Mitigation  [0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The added `size < [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m` check prevents the earlier unsigned wrap issue and stops[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39many attempt to read the [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m bytes of offset in undersized buffers.  [0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The manual loop ensures only single-byte reads occur, fully preventing [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvectorized overreads that ASAN catches.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This preserves the functional semantics: the same `s` bytes get copied, [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`entry->size` is set correctly, and we still return early on OOM.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Performance impact is minimal because most EXIF entries are small; even if [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlarge, the overhead of a simple loop is acceptable versus the risk of security [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbugs.  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No existing tests will break, since the copy semantics and error paths are [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39midentical.  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No fuzz-harness, external libraries, or test code is touched. Fuzzing entry [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpoints remain unchanged.[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. References to Similar Code  [0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The TIFF-writing counterpart [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`exif_data_save_data_entry`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m already performs [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmanual buffer management but uses `memcpy` only when expanding the output [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer—vectorization there is less risky because the buffer has guaranteed padding.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This pattern [0m[1;39m([0m[39mmanual byte-copy[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m has been used elsewhere in libexif for small, [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msensitive fields to avoid ASAN false positives.[0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis combined change fully addresses the heap-buffer-overflow under ASAN while [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpreserving valid EXIF parsing logic.  [0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAn AddressSanitizer heap-buffer-overflow was reported in libexif’s [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexif_data_load_data_entry function when the fuzzer fed a malformed buffer. The [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minitial crash occurred in a call to `[0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data, d + doff, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`, where `doff[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+ s` exceeded the allocated region. A patch was applied that:[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Added a bounds check to ensure the [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte offset field at `d + offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m` is [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39minside the input.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Replaced the multi-byte `memcpy` with a byte-wise loop copy.[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mAfter applying the patch, the fuzzer still triggers a one-byte heap-buffer-overflow[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mat the byte-wise copy site, indicating that `doff + s` can still overrun the [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer.[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. **Initial Issue**  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Crash location: `exif_data_load_data_entry` in `libexif/exif-data.c`, line [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maround [0m[1;36m213[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Error: heap-buffer-overflow on a [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m-byte read [0m[1;39m([0m[39mvia `__asan_memcpy`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m at an [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maddress just past the end of a [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte heap allocation.  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Stack trace highlights:[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • `exif_data_load_data_entry` → `exif_data_load_data_content` → [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data` → `exif_data_new_from_data`.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Allocated buffer is [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m bytes; the code computed a size `s` and an offset [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`doff`, then blindly copied `s` bytes from `d + doff` into `entry->data`.[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. **Key Observations in the Initial Log**  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The buffer region `[0m[1;39m[[0m[1;36m0x511000000180[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m bytes.  [0m            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - `memcpy` attempts to read [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes starting at [0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset right at[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe end[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No check that `doff + s` ≤ `size` existed.  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The fuzzer runs in libfuzzer mode, exercising `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput`.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. **Patch Attempt**  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `exif_data_load_data_entry`:[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Inserted variables: added `unsigned int i;`.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Wrapped the `s > [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m` branch in braces and added:[0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       – A check that `size >= [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m && offset <= size – [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m` before reading the [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moffset field; logs and returns [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m if it fails.  [0m                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Retained the existing “sanity checks” for `doff ≥ size` and `doff + s > [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msize`.  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • Changed data copy from `[0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data, d + doff, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` to a for-loop:[0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m         for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mi = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; i < s; ++i[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m             entry->data[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = d[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdoff + i[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. **Patch Result Log**  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The same heap-buffer-overflow fires, now a [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-byte overflow at [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:222[0m[39m` [0m[1;39m([0m[39minside the for-loop[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The corrupted address is again [0m[1;36m0x51100000024f[0m[39m, the first byte past the [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mallocated buffer.  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This shows that, while the multi-byte read was prevented, the code still [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattempts to read `s` bytes without ensuring `doff + s ≤ size`, leading to a [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mone-byte overrun.[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. **Areas for Further Investigation**  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The calculation of `s` [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`entry->components * component_size`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and whether it [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcan exceed the remaining buffer.  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The interplay between small [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`s ≤ [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and large [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`s > [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m formats and how [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`doff` is derived.  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The “sanity checks” after computing `doff`—particularly the test for `doff + s[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m> size`, which may not be reached or may be bypassed in some code paths.  [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Related functions in `libexif/exif-data.c`:  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • exif_data_load_data_content  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • exif_data_load_data  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     • exif_data_new_from_data  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Any other callers or consumers of entry->data that assume safe copying.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThe initial issue is a heap-buffer-overflow detected by AddressSanitizer in the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfunction `exif_data_load_data_entry` [0m[1;39m([0m[39min `libexif/exif-data.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m when processing [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfuzzed EXIF data. The overflow occurs on a multi-byte read via `memcpy`, reading [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpast an allocated [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte buffer. A patch was applied to add integer-overflow [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecks, buffer-bounds validations, and to replace `memcpy` with a byte-wise copy [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mloop. After rebuilding and running the fuzzer again, AddressSanitizer still reports[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma one-byte heap-buffer-overflow at the same code location [0m[1;39m([0m[39mnow in the byte-wise [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcopy loop[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, indicating the patch did not fully prevent out-of-bounds access.[0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Initial Issue  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The error arises during fuzz testing of `exif_from_data_fuzzer`.  [0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - AddressSanitizer reports a heap-buffer-overflow in `exif_data_load_data_entry`[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mat line [0m[1;36m213[0m[39m of `exif-data.c` when `[0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data, d + doff, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` is executed.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The allocated region for `entry->data` is [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m bytes long, but `memcpy` [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattempts to read [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m bytes at offset [0m[1;36m0x24f[0m[39m [0m[1;39m([0m[39mjust past the region[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Stack trace:  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     · `exif_data_load_data_entry` → `exif_data_load_data_content` → [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data` → `exif_data_new_from_data` → `LLVMFuzzerTestOneInput` → [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibFuzzer entry points.  [0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Patch Attempt  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - In `libexif/exif-data.c`, within `exif_data_load_data_entry`:  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     · Introduced local variable `i`.  [0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     · Computed `fsize = [0m[1;35mexif_format_get_size[0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m`.  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     · Checked for integer overflow in `fsize * entry->components` and for zero [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtotal size.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     · Added bounds check before reading the [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte offset field: verify `size >= [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m12[0m[39m` and `offset <= size - [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m`.  [0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     · Separated cases for `s > [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m` and `s <= [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m`, computing `doff` accordingly.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     · Consolidated buffer-bounds check: ensure `doff <= size` and `s <= size - [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdoff`.  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     · Replaced `[0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data, d + doff, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` with a for-loop copying one byte[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mat a time:  [0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m       for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mi = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; i < s; ++i[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m entry->data[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = d[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdoff + i[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Patch Result  [0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - After applying the patch, rerunning the fuzzer still triggers a [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheap-buffer-overflow, now a [0m[1;36m1[0m[39m-byte read at the same boundary in the copy loop [0m[1;39m([0m[39mline[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m222[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The overflow is reported immediately after copying all valid bytes, indicating[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mthe loop condition or bounds check allows one iteration too many or miscalculates [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`doff + s`.  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Stack trace after patch closely mirrors the original, pinpointing the new loop[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mas the overflow site.  [0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Areas for Further Investigation  [0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The calculation and validation of `s` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtotal data length[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m versus the actual [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mavailable bytes: verify that `s` never exceeds `size - doff`.  [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The determination of `doff` for small [0m[1;39m([0m[39m≤[0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m and large [0m[1;39m([0m[39m>[0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m values: ensure [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`doff` always points within the buffer.  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Off-by-one errors in loop bounds: confirm the for-loop iterates exactly `s` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtimes without overrun.  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Upstream parsing of EXIF headers and directory entries [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39m`exif_data_load_data_content`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m: check whether invalid tag/format values lead to [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mincorrect `components` or `offset` values.  [0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Integration points where `entry->components` and `exif_format_get_size` return[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munexpected values, triggering edge cases.[0m                                           [2m                [0m
