[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m70[0m[39m:     [0m[39mfor [0m[1;39m([0m[39mi = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; ExifFormatTable[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[39m.size; i++[0m[1;39m)[0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m71[0m[39m:     [0m[39m        [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39mExifFormatTable[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[39m.format == format[0m[1;39m)[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m72[0m[39m:     [0m[39m        [0m[39m        [0m[39mreturn ExifFormatTable[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[39m.size;[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m73[0m[39m:     [0m[39mreturn [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m74[0m[39m:[0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Overview  [0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   The residual one-byte overflow after the last patch indicates an off-by-one or [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munsigned arithmetic edge in the two-phase “doff > size” [0m[35m/[0m[39m “s > size - doff” checks.[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mWe will simplify and harden all size arithmetic by:[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   a[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Using a [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m-bit intermediate for multiplication and addition to prevent [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwrap/overflow.  [0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   b[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Centralizing bounds checks into single comparisons of `[0m[1;39m([0m[39muint64_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m offset + X [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<= size` for header reads, and `[0m[1;39m([0m[39muint64_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m doff + s <= size` for data reads.  [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   c[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m Ensuring we always verify that reading the [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m-byte directory entry header is [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39msafe before touching any bytes at `d+offset+N`.  [0m                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Detailed Steps  [0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   A. Change local temporaries to [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m-bit for safety  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Declare `uint64_t fsize64 = [0m[1;35mexif_format_get_size[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->format[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Declare `uint64_t comp64 = entry->components;`  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Compute `uint64_t total64 = fsize64 * comp64;`  [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - After guarding multiplication overflow [0m[1;39m([0m[39msee B[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, cast to `size_t s = [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m total64;` for allocation and loops.  [0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   B. Multiplication overflow & zero-length checks  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - If `comp64 != [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m && fsize64 > UINT64_MAX [0m[35m/[0m[39m comp64` → overflow → `return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;` [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - If `total64 == [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m` → no data → `return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;`  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   C. Header-read bounds checks  [0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - We unconditionally read [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m bytes of tag/format/components: ensure `offset + [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m8[0m[39m <= size`. If not, `return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;`.  [0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - For external-data [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`s > [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, we read a [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte offset at `d + offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m … [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+[0m[1;36m11[0m[39m`: ensure `offset + [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m <= size`. If not, `return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;`.  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   D. Data-read bounds check [0m[1;39m([0m[39munified[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m  [0m                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - After computing `uint64_t doff64` either from inline [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m or [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mexternal [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`exif_get_long`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, check `doff64 + s <= size`.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        - If false, log a debug message and `return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;`.  [0m                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   E. Data allocation & copy  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Allocate exactly `s` bytes via existing `[0m[1;35mexif_data_alloc[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;`  [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m      - Copy via a safe for-loop `for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mi = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; i < s; ++i[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m entry->data[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = d[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdoff64[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+ i[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;`  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Preservation of Existing Logic  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We keep the same control flow—calculating `s`, determining `doff` for inline [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mvs external data, allocating buffer, and copying bytes.  [0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - We retain the integer-overflow guard and zero-size guard.  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Debug logging remains focused on “entry header past end” or “entry data out of[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuffer” scenarios.  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Rationale and Side-Effect Mitigation  [0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Using a single [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m-bit check `[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff64 + s <= size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` removes subtle off-by-one [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mgaps inherent in two separate unsigned comparisons.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Promoting to [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m-bit for intermediate arithmetic ensures no silent wrap-around [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mif a malicious EXIF header uses very large component counts.  [0m                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Early header-bounds checks guarantee safety for all subsequent reads [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtag, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mformat, components, offset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - The patch does not alter fuzz harnesses, test code, or external [0m               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mdependencies—only the vulnerable parsing function.  [0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No functionality is removed; EXIF entries remain parsed identically when [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mwell-formed.  [0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Potential performance impact from [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m-bit arithmetic is negligible in the [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcontext of EXIF parsing.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. High-Level Patch Outline  [0m                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```diff[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m--- a/libexif/exif-data.c[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+++ b/libexif/exif-data.c[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m@@ [0m[1;36m-164[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m7[0m[39m +[0m[1;36m164[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m12[0m[39m @@ static int[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m exif_data_load_data_entry [0m[1;39m([0m[39mExifData *data, ExifEntry *entry,[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                            const unsigned char *d,[0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m                            unsigned int size, unsigned int offset[0m[1;39m)[0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-   unsigned int s, doff;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+   uint64_t fsize64, comp64, total64;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+   size_t   s;[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+   uint64_t doff64;[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+   unsigned int i;[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+[0m                                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    entry->tag        = exif_get_short [0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset + [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m, data->priv->order[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    entry->format     = exif_get_short [0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset + [0m[1;36m2[0m[39m, data->priv->order[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    entry->components = exif_get_long  [0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset + [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m, data->priv->order[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m@@ [0m[1;36m-180[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m10[0m[39m +[0m[1;36m185[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m32[0m[39m @@ exif_data_load_data_entry [0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Compute total byte-count: format-size * component-count *[0m[35m/[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-   s = [0m[1;35mexif_format_get_size[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->format[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m * entry->components;[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-   if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39ms < entry->components[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m || [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m[1;39m)[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+   [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Use [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m-bit to prevent wrap *[0m[35m/[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+   fsize64 = [0m[1;35mexif_format_get_size[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->format[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+   comp64  = entry->components;[0m                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+   if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mcomp64 != [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m && fsize64 > UINT64_MAX [0m[35m/[0m[39m comp64[0m[1;39m)[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+   total64 = fsize64 * comp64;[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+   if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtotal64 == [0m[1;36m0[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+       return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+   s = [0m[1;39m([0m[39msize_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m total64;[0m                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+   [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Ensure we can read the [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m-byte header [0m[1;39m([0m[39mtag/format/components[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m *[0m[35m/[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+   if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39muint64_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39moffset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m > size[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+       return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[35m/[0m[39m*[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m@@ [0m[1;36m-189[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m6[0m[39m +[0m[1;36m216[0m[39m,[0m[1;36m22[0m[39m @@ exif_data_load_data_entry [0m[1;39m([0m[33m...[0m[1;39m)[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-   if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-       doff = exif_get_long [0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m, data->priv->order[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-   else[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-       doff = offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m;[0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+   if [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+       [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Ensure safe [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte read for external offset *[0m[35m/[0m                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+       if [0m[1;39m([0m[1;39m([0m[39muint64_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39moffset + [0m[1;36m12[0m[39m > size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+           [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+                    [0m[32m"Entry offset field past end [0m[32m([0m[32m%u+12 > %u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m,[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+                    offset, size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+           return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+       [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+       doff64 = [0m[1;35mexif_get_long[0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m, data->priv->order[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+   [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+       [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Inline small data *[0m[35m/[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+       doff64 = [0m[1;39m([0m[39muint64_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39moffset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m;[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+   [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Unified bounds check: data region [0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdoff64 .. doff64+s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m must fit *[0m[35m/[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+   if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdoff64 + s > size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+       [0m[1;35mexif_log[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, EXIF_LOG_CODE_DEBUG, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m,[0m                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+                [0m[32m"Entry data out of buffer [0m[32m([0m[32moff+[0m[32mlen[0m[32m=%"[0m[39m PRIu64 [0m[32m" > %u[0m[32m)[0m[32m"[0m[39m,[0m             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+                doff64 + [0m[1;39m([0m[39muint64_t[0m[1;39m)[0m[39ms, size[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+       return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+   [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    entry->data = exif_data_alloc [0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    if [0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        entry->size = s;[0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[35m/[0m[39m* Safe byte-wise copy *[0m[35m/[0m                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-       for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mi = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; i < s; ++i[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m-           entry->data[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = d[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdoff + i[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+       for [0m[1;39m([0m[39mi = [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m; i < s; ++i[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+           entry->data[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mi[0m[1;39m][0m[39m = d[0m[1;39m[[0m[39mdoff64 + i[0m[1;39m][0m[39m;[0m                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m    [0m[1;39m}[0m[39m else [0m[1;39m{[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        [0m[1;35mEXIF_LOG_NO_MEMORY[0m[1;39m([0m[39mdata->priv->log, [0m[32m"ExifData"[0m[39m, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m        return [0m[1;36m0[0m[39m;[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m===Evaluation [0m[33mReport[0m[39m===[0m                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m# Evaluation Report[0m                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Summary[0m                                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mA libFuzzer invocation of `exif_from_data_fuzzer` on a single-input testcase [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mtriggered an AddressSanitizer-detected heap-buffer-overflow in [0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry` within `libexif/exif-data.c`. The overflow occurred [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mduring a `memcpy` of entry data past the end of an allocated buffer. A patch [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mattempt introduced [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m-bit arithmetic to compute and check sizes, added bounds [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mchecks on header and data regions, replaced the `memcpy` with a byte-wise copy, and[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mreplaced the variables `s` and `doff` with new [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m-bit equivalents [0m[1;39m([0m[39m`total64`, [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`doff64`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m. After applying the patch, the build failed with an “undeclared [0m          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39midentifier ‘doff’” error at a later reference to `doff`.[0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Description[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mInitial Issue  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• Fuzzing logs report:  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - ERROR: AddressSanitizer: heap-buffer-overflow on address …  [0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The overflow happens in `__asan_memcpy` called by `exif_data_load_data_entry` [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mline [0m[1;36m213[0m[39m of `exif-data.c`[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - The read of size [0m[1;36m16[0m[39m at offset just past a [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m-byte region indicates an [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mout-of-bounds data copy when reading EXIF tag data.  [0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Call stack shows the issue originates from `exif_data_new_from_data` → [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data` → `exif_data_load_data_content` → [0m                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry`.  [0m                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - A region allocated via `malloc` of size [0m[1;36m207[0m[39m bytes was overrun by attempting to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcopy more bytes than fit.  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mPatch Attempt  [0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• Variables and types introduced:  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Declared `unsigned long long fsize64, comp64, total64, doff64; size_t s; [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39munsigned int i;`  [0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Removed original `unsigned int s, doff;` declarations.  [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• Added checks and logic:  [0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Early return if `offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m` exceeds buffer size [0m[1;39m([0m[39mguard reading tag header[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Compute `fsize64 = [0m[1;35mexif_format_get_size[0m[1;39m([0m[39mformat[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` and `comp64 = components`, [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcheck for multiplication overflow, set `total64 = fsize64 * comp64`, reject zero or[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39moverflow.  [0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Cast `total64` to `size_t s`.  [0m                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Determine data offset: if `s > [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m`, read `doff64` from the [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m-byte field [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwith [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mheader bounds check[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m, else `doff64 = offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m`.  [0m                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Unified bound check: reject if `doff64 + s` exceeds buffer size.  [0m              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - Replace `[0m[1;35mmemcpy[0m[1;39m([0m[39mentry->data, d + doff, s[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m` with a for-loop copying byte by byte[0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mfrom `d + doff64`.  [0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• Compilation failure:  [0m                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - A later assignment in the file, `data->priv->offset_mnote = doff;`, was not [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mupdated to use `doff64`.  [0m                                                          [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m  - This caused “use of undeclared identifier ‘doff’” at line [0m[1;36m247[0m[39m, aborting the [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mbuild.  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mParts to Investigate  [0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• The function `exif_data_load_data_entry` in `libexif/exif-data.c`: review all [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39muses of `doff` and adjacent logic for external vs. inline data, including logging [0m  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcalls.  [0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• References to `offset_mnote` and any other consumers of the `doff` variable [0m      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39melsewhere in the codebase.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• Surrounding code in `exif-data.c` that handles metadata offsets, to ensure [0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mconsistent handling of [0m[1;36m32[0m[39m-bit vs. [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m-bit values.  [0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m• The interaction between `exif_data_load_data_content` and [0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`exif_data_load_data_entry` in cases of non-standard or truncated EXIF blocks.  [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mThis investigation will help achieve a complete understanding of buffer bounds [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mhandling and correct the compilation error in the patch attempt.[0m                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Initial Issue Log[0m                                                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mHere is the initial issue log of the codebase:[0m                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<issue>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+ [0m[33mFUZZER[0m[39m=[0m[35mexif_from_data_fuzzer[0m                                                      [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [39m+ [0m[32m'[0m[32m[[0m[32m'[0m[39m [0m[32m'!'[0m[39m -v TESTCASE [0m[32m'[0m[32m][0m[32m'[0m                                                           [2m                [0m

[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m189[0m[39m:    [0m[39m * Size? If bigger than [0m[1;36m4[0m[39m bytes, the actual data is not[0m                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m190[0m[39m:    [0m[39m * in the entry but somewhere else [0m[1;39m([0m[39moffset[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.[0m                                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m191[0m[39m:    [0m[39m *[0m[35m/[0m                                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m192[0m[39m:    [0m[39mif [0m[1;39m([0m[39ms > [0m[1;36m4[0m[1;39m)[0m                                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m193[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mdoff = exif_get_long [0m[1;39m([0m[39md + offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m, data->priv->order[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m;[0m           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m194[0m[39m:    [0m[39melse[0m                                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m195[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mdoff = offset + [0m[1;36m8[0m[39m;[0m                                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<code>[0m                                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlibexif/exif-data.[0m[1;92mc:232[0m[39m-[0m[1;36m234[0m                                                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m232[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m233[0m[39m:    [0m[39m        [0m[39mdata->priv->offset_mnote = doff;[0m                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m234[0m[39m:    [0m[1;39m}[0m                                                                           [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m```[0m                                                                                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode[0m[39m>[0m                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mcode_snippets[0m[39m>[0m                                                                    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m## Fix Strategy[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<fix_strategy>[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m1[0m[39m. Reapply the [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m-bit–based bounds‐checking patch in `exif_data_load_data_entry` [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;39m([0m[39mthe changes introducing `fsize64`, `comp64`, `total64`, `doff64`, replacing the [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mold `unsigned int doff`, and switching the `memcpy` to a byte‐wise copy[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m2[0m[39m. Locate the assignment of the maker‐note offset near line [0m[1;36m232[0m[39m in [0m                 [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m`libexif/exif-data.c`:[0m                                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     data->priv->offset_mnote = doff;[0m                                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m3[0m[39m. Update this line to use the new [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m‐bit offset variable, casting down to the [0m     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m32[0m[39m‐bit field:[0m                                                                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     data->priv->offset_mnote = [0m[1;39m([0m[39munsigned int[0m[1;39m)[0m[39mdoff64;[0m                               [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m     ```[0m                                                                            [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   This resolves the “undeclared identifier ‘doff’” compilation error while [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mpreserving the previously added overflow and bounds checks.[0m                         [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m4[0m[39m. Search the rest of `exif_data_load_data_entry` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mand nearby helper functions[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m to [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mensure no remaining references to `doff` remain; all should now use `doff64` [0m[1;39m([0m[39mwith [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mappropriate casts only when assigning to a smaller‐width storage[0m[1;39m)[0m[39m.  [0m                [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m5[0m[39m. Rebuild and run the full test and fuzz harness:[0m                                  [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Confirms the build error is gone.[0m                                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Verifies no regressions in existing functionality.[0m                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Ensures the original heap‐buffer‐overflow is still guarded by the [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m‐bit size [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mmultiplications and unified bounds checks introduced earlier.[0m                       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m6[0m[39m. Potential side‐effects & mitigation:[0m                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - Casting from [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m‐bit to [0m[1;36m32[0m[39m‐bit for `offset_mnote` is safe because we already [0m   [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mcheck `doff64 + s <= size`, and the overall buffer size and offsets originate from [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39ma [0m[1;36m32[0m[39m‐bit `size` parameter.  [0m                                                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No other code paths rely on the old [0m[1;36m32[0m[39m‐bit `doff` variable in this function.  [0m [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - No harness or test code is modified; the fuzzer logic remains unchanged.[0m       [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [1;36m7[0m[39m. Conclusion:[0m                                                                      [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - This minimal change directly addresses the compilation failure without [0m        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39maltering external libraries, harness code, or tests.  [0m                              [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m   - It preserves all the [0m[1;36m64[0m[39m‐bit overflow protection and the new byte‐wise copy [0m    [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39mlogic, ensuring no regressions in security or functionality.[0m                        [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m                                                                                             [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         [39m<[0m[35m/[0m[95mfix_strategy[0m[1m>[0m                                                                     [2m                [0m
[2;36m                    [0m         ===Evaluation [33mEnd[0m===                                                                [2m                [0m
